<TITLE> President leaves for Turkey to attend OIC summit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)President Zillur Rahman left Dhaka Friday morning for Istanbul, Turkey, to attend an OIC summit on economic and commercial cooperation to be held there. The president's press secretary Abdul Awal Hawladar told bdnews24.com that the president flew out of ZIA at 10:40am aboard an Emirates flight. He will be reaching Istanbul on Saturday via Dubai where he will have an overnight stop. The Istanbul summit will be held on Nov 9 to mark the 25th anniversary of the OIC standing committee. In addition to attending the summit, Zillur will perform ziarat at the grave of Hazrat Yup Sultan Ansari in Istanbul. He will also visit the famous Topkapi museum. The president is scheduled to meet his Turkish counterpart Abdullah Ghul during his visit. Finance minister AMA Muhith, agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury, the three chiefs of the defence forces and senior government officials were present at the airport to see the president off. President Zillur Rahman is scheduled to return home on the evening of Nov 11. bd
